reason.tex:
%text We can infer the following % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{NNN}
\hline \text{Equation} & \text{Vertex at} & y\text{ defined if} \\ \hline y = \sqrt{2-x} & (2,0) & x \leq 2 \\ \hline y = \sqrt{x} & (0,0) & x \geq 0 \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text And hence we can see that % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{Nl}
\hline \text{Expression} & Meaning \\ \hline \int_0^2 \sqrt{2-x}\cdot dx & Area from $0\to 2 = P+R$ \\ \hline \int_0^2 \sqrt{x}\cdot dx & Area from $0\to 2 = Q+R$ \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text Moreover % \begin{align}
\int_0^2 \sqrt{2-x}\cdot dx &= \underbrace{\int_0^2 \sqrt{2- \left(2-x \right)}\cdot dx}_{\int_0^a f(x) dx = \int_0^a f (a-x)\cdot dx} \\ &= \int_0^2 \sqrt{x}\cdot dx \\ \therefore P+R &= Q + R \\ \text{or } P &= Q \end{align} %text %
